{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place butter, shallots and garlic into mixing bowl and chop <nobr>3 sec\/speed 7<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula, and sauté <nobr>3 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Add 7.5 oz water, stock paste and 1 tsp peppercorns into mixing bowl. Insert simmering basket, weigh in potatoes and cook <nobr>10 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<\/nobr>. Meanwhile, place a large oiled frying pan over med-high heat and season lamb with salt and pepper. Once the pan is hot, sear lamb on both sides (approx. 1-2 minutes each side) until lightly browned.","Transfer seared lamb into Varoma dish and onto Varoma tray and set Varoma aside. Place 1 tbsp water into hot frying pan and stir over heat to de-glaze the pan. Turn off heat and allow pan to cool on stove top.","Arrange asparagus and carrots around seared lamb in Varoma dish and on Varoma tray, place Varoma into position, secure Varoma lid and cook <nobr>4 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<\/nobr>. Lamb will be cooked medium-rare. If desired, continue cooking until lamb, asparagus, carrots and potatoes are cooked to your liking.","Transfer lamb, vegetables and potatoes onto a serving plate or large bowl and cover to rest and keep warm. The lamb will continue to cook as it rests. Reserve stock in mixing bowl.","In the measuring cup, combine whisky and corn starch together, and set aside.","Add remaining 1 tsp peppercorns, cream, reserved pan juices and reserved whisky and corn starch mixture to stock in mixing bowl and without measuring cup, reduce <nobr>10-12 min\/195°F\/\/speed <\/nobr>.","Slice lamb and serve with potatoes, carrots and asparagus, drizzled with pink peppercorn sauce."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["1 oz unsalted butter, diced (½ in.-1 in.)","2 shallot (approx. 1 oz ea), peeled, halved","2 garlic cloves","7 ½ oz water, plus 1 tbsp, divided","½ tsp meat stock paste, to taste (see Tip)","2 tsp pink peppercorns, divided","10 ½ oz potatoes, small, unpeeled, washed and cubed (½ in.-1 in.)","olive oil, to grease","16 - 24 oz lamb sirloins, boneless (approx. 3-6 fillets)","1 pinch salt","1 pinch ground black pepper","1 bunch green asparagus (5-7 oz), trimmed and halved","1 carrot, large, julienned","1 tbsp whisky,","1 tsp corn starch","2 oz heavy whipping cream"]}],"id":"r106909","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-c3qY2m2XbkE\/XZQxlBhyzII\/AAAAAAAAcwY\/YB7RTx_VEmghKUTktZydq5OYJxpkZCbPgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_sLn9e42P2ILNDWjg.png","title":"Lamb Fillets with Pink Peppercorn Sauce","publishedAt":"2017-03-17T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"29 g","fat":"29.3 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"12.8 g","calories":"1830 kJ \/ 435 kcal"},"usefulItems":"frying pan, serving plate, stove","hintsAndTricks":["USDA recommends cooking lamb to an internal temperature of 145°F followed by a 3 minute rest.","To make your own meat stock paste: refer to The Basic Cookbook for the Meat Stock Paste recipe.","Pink peppercorns can be found at specialty grocery stores.","Small potatoes e.g., new potatoes or fingerlings."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","30m","4 portions"]}